Pretty neat, hip little spot. Parking is tight - you'll have to rely on metered street parking (free after 6pm), public lots, or a garage.  The cocktail menu is a bit on the small side, but they have a decent selection of whisk(e)y, wine, and beer.  Worth a second try!

Love the atmosphere here! Small menu which I love to see. Great wine selection. Ordered farro risotto because I wanted to see how it was accomplished and was not disappointed! Dessert of salted caramel gelato was a great note to end on.

I've already been here twice in 2 weeks and I'm going to keep coming back because it's a great place for catching up with friends. However, there are a few things I'm hoping will get fixed.  1) Wait staff needs to chill a little. Give the party time to settle in - allow them space to make small talk, check out the menu, ask each other questions, deliberate on what they want to eat. During both of my visits, my full party hadn't arrived but those of us who were there ordered drinks as we waited. The wait staff kept coming by to check on us when it was obvious we were waiting for another guest. And, we were occupied with our drinks. They were just over zealous to make sure we were OK (which is not a bad thing and is much better than being ignored),  2) Temperature - the restaurant temperature was on the colder side during my first visit and it made the food go cold super fast. During my second visit, the temperature was a little better.  3) Timing - we ordered an appetizer but it came out with main course.  3) Bell dinging - when orders are ready to be served, the kitchen staff dings a bell which I'm assuming is to get the wait staff's attention (during my first visit, they hit a gong - no joke, it only happened once while i was there though). But the bell dinging makes me feel like I'm at a truck-stop diner - it's cool but it doesn't fit the restaurant atmosphere, so the noise really stood out to me.  That list of demands isn't so bad, right?  So, what did I love? I'll definitely return for the Farro Risotto. It wasn't mushy or too cheese-y - it was absolutely perfect. And, I was stoked to see a Rogue Sour Beer on their drink menu.

Italian inspired cuisine infused with local flavors and ingredients, creative cocktails, plus indoor/outdoor dining - right across the street from the famed Hawaii Theatre in the Arts District near Downtown/Chinatown. Perfect spot to meet up for pau hana, dinner before or after a show (and soon, open for lunch)!  Pro tip: host your group event in the private bar/ dining room behind the open air patio.
